<span class="name"><a name="2781"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#1:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>HorzaHarshom</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=2781&amp;sid=feb8d18aa48ae053890f3905027c8ea6#2781"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Thu Nov 07, 2002 10:16 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
	<span class="gensmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;----</span><br>

<span class="postbody">Talisman of Shadoo/Jasinth- Two low-use utility spells are too many for our sparse 60+ line up.  Combine them both into a single spell, and add a stam regen component.  Call it 'Fortitude of the Wild' or something similiar.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Acumen - Move it to 61, or just get rid off it.  A vision spell has no place as one of our level 65 spells.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Plague - With its super long duration, it's useless in groups and most solo fights.  1k damage over two minutes is horrendous, considering that Scorpion Venom does over 700 in 40 seconds.  While I realize they stack, that doesn't change the fact that plague is sub-par for 65.  Chance the duration to something more reasonable, say 12 ticks, and increase the damage by about 50%.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Frost Spear - Increase the damage to 750, giving it a 3:1 ratio, the same as our other cold DDs. I can accept the fact that they don't improve in ratio, but having them get worse is ridiculous.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Arag's Celerity - As it stands, this buff is hardly better than Sha's Ferocity, as it has the same haste %.  Increase the haste to 100%, or add some other bonus to it.  Say, an innate chance to proc more, or a couple hundred HP.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Ferocity - Still nothing but a toy, just like Savagery.  The bonus damage from ATK is not worth having to spend a huge chunk of mana and a peridot every 6 minutes.  If it were a group spell, or lasted half an hour, that would be understandable.  Raid use?  Insignificant.  Letting two rogues do slightly more damage should not be our role on raids.  And extra atk isn't going to help the MT hold aggro.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Spirit of Rellic - All we get is a very minor damage upgrade?  Give it a low-resist over the cap stun, or mana drain, anything to differentiate it.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
 <i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
